			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Manda,<BR>
  First off, I am not here to bash you. There are just a few things I do take exception to.<BR>
<BR>
1. You claimed that EQ is an addiction because he spent so much time doing it and want a warning label on it. Following that train of thought, shouldn't we have warning labels on TV, horseback rides, and of course I would need to put the warning on my fiancee because I would rather spend time with her than I would a game. Then again, I would also need to put warning labels on my daughters, because I would rather play games with them to sit like a zombie. <BR>
<BR>
Do I play EQ alot. Umm oh hell yeah I do. I do it after my real life stuff has been done. I can decide what is important. The people that have no life because of EQ had problems before EQ. If they weren't playing EQ it would be gambling, drugs, TV, women/men. It doesn't matter what someone is doing if they have an addictive personality.<BR>
<BR>
You stated that you have recieved some not so nice email since the article, well I had joined your email list to see if I could help but what I found is that the members of your list who attacked people with being named moderators? Hmm, so on your list it was ok for a couple to use language that hasn't been used here. You are allowed to stop anyone from disagreeing with you but you don't want to hear it on a &quot;EVERQUEST&quot; board? I watched as people who had a different opinion of your members, get attacked, insulted and swore at. To me, that is worse than an &quot;addiction&quot; to EQ. That shows little manners or a desire to understand something. Some of the EQers that posted in your group were indeed a horses ass and I don't condone what they were saying, but others were just trying to help both groups understand. Your forum seemed to have everyone blaming EQ, but whenever anyone mentioned maybe the relationship had problems other than EQ, they were vilified. That in itself shows there is a major problem. Take a look at the post in your own mailing list with an objective eye and tell me what you see.<BR>
<BR>
Personally, if my fiancee does anything that takes away from our time and ruins the relationship, guess what?, out the door she goes. If your partner isn't working on the relationship with you, dump them, they aren't good enough in the first place. This does seem as if you are putting the blame on EQ, but I think the blame has to be placed on the partner who being selfish.<BR>
<BR>
My fiancee not only doesn't mind me playing, she bought me a second copy of EQ-Kunark, and yes, she even bought me two copies of SoV. I mostly play when I wake up before her or on the nights when I can't sleep.<BR>
<BR>
If I don't have to work and my fiancee is either asleep or working, do I sit in front of the computer and play, yep sure do. Where else for $10 a month, can I talk to people from England, Sweden, Germany or any of the other locations? Chat? Well, then someone would form a group calling us chat addicts. Its a no-win sitution. A lot of people would rather blame someting than to look at a relationship they are in. Still not an attack on you. I have my priorities correct. My family comes first. I even shut down to visit with my future inlaws. :-) <BR>
<BR>
You can point to the father who let his child die to playing, but he could just have easily been watching tv, doing drugs, sleeping with the neighbor or any of a number of things. Does it bother me that a child died? Yes. When an adult places a game over a fiancee, does that bother me? No. That would fall into the catorgorie that the fiancee either needs to get a clue or get dumped. To the people on your list, I do hope everything works out but getting rid of EQ won't solve the problem for them. Thats when both partners need to seek counseling for the relationship.<BR>
<BR>
One last thing, to the member on your list who says that(not exact words) &quot;He ate so much candy and sode while playing EQ that he got diabetes and now I have to chase him around making sure he doesn't sneak candy&quot; please pass on that <BR>
1. That wouldn't &quot;cause&quot; diabetes. It may have caused a diabetic episode which made them aware that he was borderline diabetic.<BR>
2. If you have to chase him around to make sure he doesn't sneak, there is a problem. If he is an adult, you shouldn't have to treat him like a little child. Stop mothering him. He can make his own decisions.<BR>
<BR>
How do I know about diabetes? My fiancee has lived with it for most of her life. To try and blame EQ for a medical condition is pathetic. Post real arguements and I would be more than glad to discuss this with ANY of your members, but to post something like that as a case against EQ or anything for that matter is the quickest way to get me fired up.<BR>
<BR>
Most of my guild does play alot, I look forward to signing on to see my friends here. They are more like an extended family to me. I have watched as some great friendships have been made.<BR>
<BR>
Thats all from me. If you would like to really discuss this without using sensationalism, in other words, don't play the game the misinformed reporter did, I will be more than happy to talk to you or your members. Who knows, maybe I can help.<BR>
<BR>
Dayylin<BR>
Guildleader- Heralds of the Gods<BR>
Cazic-Thule
