	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I hit 47 a few weeks ago after playing for over 18 months.  I'm engaged, getting married in June and although she never said anything, I'm sure that my fiancee was upset about me playing for hours on end every night.<BR>
<BR>
47 levels.  47 levels of doing the same old nonsense, day in, day out.  47 levels of listening to increasingly whining, begging young idiots who *truly* have no life outside EQ.<BR>
<BR>
It's been three weeks now since I last played, and I must say I haven't missed it a bit.<BR>
<BR>
To all those guys and girls who are spending inordinate amounts of time playing a game instead of being with your hunny - think about what you're doing.  In 10, 15, 20 years, whenever the plug is finally pulled on the EverQuest servers and you look back at all the missed opportunities, all the times your significant other went to bed alone harbouring thoughts of resentment to you and the game and all you've got to show for your efforts is the memory of a level 60/70/80 character and the countless hours of sitting in one spot camping some uber loot, think about the person, the real, live, fun person you abandoned and who finally wizened up and left you.<BR>
<BR>
I'm not saying &quot;quit the game&quot;.  All I'm saying is have consideration for your lover (if you have one) or your parents or your friends.  EQ is just a silly game.  Don't ruin your life or anyone elses for some average looking polygons.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
