	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well... I am going to have to agree with a few folks on the thought train that EQ is a game, and it is PEOPLE who make decisions about their lives.  I realize there are many people who for one reason or another have never really cultivated some self control in their lives.  Perhaps its upbringing or any number of other factors, but I really really advocate anyone and everyone, whether an EQ player or not, to TAKE RESPONSIBILITY for YOUR Life. <BR>
<BR>
No one alse can do this for you.<BR>
Period.<BR>
<BR>
In these cases where someone loses it and gets tunnelvisioned on whatever habit or hiding place they have found, and lets their life/wife/kids etc... go to crap....  Well I just have to say the problem lies in their lack of really WANTING to see whats going on in their lives.  A person who wants greater relationships and a greater love life (or say children...) does NOT loose control of their being and get tunneled into some game.<BR>
<BR>
I began playing everquest myself as a way to reconnect with a group of friends that were my saving grace through High School and beyond, but who, for one reason or another, ended up scattered to the 4 winds.  Some got married, One joined the military, I hitched accross the country, another went to Africa in the Peace corpse...  Does this sound like People with no lives?  We have all reconnected well and don't play nearly like we all did when we were so stoked to hook up.<BR>
Granted... My &quot;Girlfriend&quot; has never understood the game and at some points has been irritated or confused just because she doesn't understand in HER life how fantasy games could be a release... Which is fine.  We hang out a lot and have a great time together, and we have just found ways to spend a lot of time together without my playing or her frustration ruining our moments together.<BR>
<BR>
Balance is a key word to me.  I feel like anything one does in their life they can either be flowing into greater balance or drifting more and more out of balance.  It is each persons job to pay attention to where they are at...  and it is NOT Verants job...  When people want to begin being more accountable for their own lives, then these situations will become less and less common.<BR>
<BR>
On a closing note... though this is a valid topic certainly... I find EQ to be a ridiculous example though I know many folk do play probably too much for their own health.  When drinking kills (KILLS!!!!) 1000's of peeps a day... and bulemia and anorexia and drug addiction and TV and polotics and all the other sick things on this planet are allowed by US to ruin our lives, then we the human family suffer.  EQ is last on the list guys...<BR>
<BR>
Thanks for reading.<BR>
Be well - Be yourself<BR>
Eliki
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
